<div ana="#b1" corresp="#jeru0012.transcription" type="translation" xml:id="jeru0012.translation">
<p>Shim'on, son of Alexa</p>
</div>
</body>
<back>
<div type="commentary">
<p>The ossuary has low feet and a vaulted lid. Height refers to height of chest plus that of lid. Ornamentation consists of two metopes and a broadened triglyph containing a branch on the chest's front side. Within each metope, an eight-petalled rosette with heart-shaped petals sits inside a whirl-rosette that is surrounded by a zigzag circle. Metopes have a disc in each corner as well. There are several proposed readings of the second name in this inscription: Sukenik reads יוסף; Savignac and Lidzbarski read יואמץ; Naveh is supported by Rahmani in his reading אלכסא, as a contraction of Alexandros.</p>
</div>
